  <h2>Tips for Managing Multiple Bots</h2>

  <h3>Naming Convention</h3>
  <p>Use consistent naming for instances and bots:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>EC2: <code>openclaw-claudia</code>, <code>openclaw-alfred</code>, <code>openclaw-jarvis</code></li>
    <li>Telegram: <code>@ClaudiaAssistantBot</code>, <code>@AlfredButlerBot</code>, <code>@JarvisAIBot</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Different Purposes</h3>
  <p>Each bot can specialize:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Personal assistant bot</li>
    <li>Code review bot</li>
    <li>Customer support bot</li>
    <li>Home automation bot</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cost Optimization</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Use <code>t3.micro</code> or <code>t3.small</code> for light-duty bots</li>
    <li>Consider spot instances for non-critical bots</li>
    <li>Stop instances when not in use (bots go offline but data persists)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Shared Resources</h3>
  <p>Consider sharing:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Same security group</li>
    <li>Same SSH key</li>
    <li>Same Claude API key (if within rate limits)</li>
  </ul>

